{
  "id": "phekb-venous-thromboembolism-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "venous-thromboembolism",
  "name": "Venous Thromboembolism - Diagnosis Code Query (DVT + PE)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find VTE patients via diagnosis codes. VTE encompasses two main entities: deep venous thrombosis (DVT \u2014 most commonly in proximal lower extremity veins) and pulmonary embolism (PE). The Synthea module distributes patients across DVT (parent), iliofemoral DVT (extent-specific), inferior vena cava thrombosis, PE, and venous embolism (NOS). An LLM querying only one code will miss substantial fraction.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients with a diagnosis of venous thromboembolism, including deep vein thrombosis (DVT) of the lower extremities, iliofemoral DVT, inferior vena cava thrombosis, and pulmonary embolism (PE).",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with blood clots.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of venous thromboembolism (VTE) \u2014 including deep vein thrombosis of lower extremities (proximal DVT, popliteal/femoral/iliofemoral), inferior vena cava thrombosis, and pulmonary embolism (PE).",
    "expert": "I need to identify all VTE patients. VTE is documented under multiple SNOMED codes from the Joint Commission VTE value set (OID 2.16.840.1.113883.3.117.1.7.1.330): Deep venous thrombosis (128053003) is the parent DVT concept, with extent-specific variants Iliofemoral DVT (234044007) and Inferior vena cava thrombosis (281595001). Pulmonary embolism (59282003) is the parent PE concept, and Venous embolism (234049002) is a NOS catch-all. Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "algorithm_path": "diagnosis-path",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Patients with VTE diagnosis codes (Paths A and B). Tests anatomic-extent and DVT-vs-PE code variation.",
